The paper discusses the adoption of machine learning in healthcare, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on explaining neural networks, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The need for transparency in healthcare also involves issues of privacy and security (cs.CY) and potentially involves the use of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the accessibility of the proposed evaluation method, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
